9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 745, L.D. 1126, “An Act Requiring
10 Serial Numbers on Firearms and Prohibiting Undetectable Firearms”
11 Amend the bill by inserting before section 1 the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 17-A MRSA §1060 is enacted to read:
13 §1060. Undetectable firearms prohibited
14 1. Definition. As used in this section, "undetectable firearm" means a firearm that can
15 operate while in a form that is not as detectable as a security exemplar, as defined in 18
16 United States Code, Section 922(p)(2)(C), and that is constructed of 3.7 ounces of material
17 type 17-4 PH stainless steel in a shape resembling a handgun, as defined in 18 United States
18 Code, Section 921(a)(30).
19 2. Undetectable firearms prohibited. A person may not:
20 A. Manufacture or cause to be manufactured within this State, import into this State or
21 offer or expose for sale, sell or transfer an undetectable firearm; or
22 B. Intentionally or knowingly possess an undetectable firearm.
23 3. Violations. The following penalties apply to violations of this section.
24 A. A person who manufactures or causes to be manufactured within this State, who
25 imports into this State or who offers or exposes for sale, sells or transfers an
26 undetectable firearm commits a Class C crime.
27 B. A person who intentionally or knowingly possesses an undetectable firearm
28 commits a Class D crime.'
29 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 5.
30 Amend the bill in section 6 in c. 253-A in §2037 by striking out all of subsection 1
31 (page 3, lines 11 to 28 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
32 '1. Prohibited conduct. A person may not:
